# Claros Design Rule

- Read `DESIGN.md` before any UI/UX change.
- Treat `DESIGN.md` as the source of truth for:
  - brand language
  - layout and hierarchy
  - interaction contracts (scrub/ring/hero)
  - motion and performance constraints
  - privacy-reality alignment
- If implementation and docs diverge, update both `DESIGN.md` and `CLAUDE.md` in the same change.
- Apply a ruthless-update policy: remove stale guidance, compress repetition, and keep instructions token-efficient.
- Prefer concise actionable bullets over paragraphs when updating docs or rules.
